cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper is about evolutionary optimization, which is a subfield of machine learning and optimization. The most relevant sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which focuses on the development and analysis of neural networks and evolutionary algorithms. The paper also discusses discrete optimization, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper proposes a new measure of convergence rate, which is relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's focus on optimization and convergence rates is also relevant to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
